  "prompt": "What should I wear when I make American Girl doll tube tops and skirts out of socks?",
  "response": "This is a fun project! Since you're making American Girl doll clothes from socks, here's what to consider wearing while you do it, balancing practicality with perhaps a touch of playful crafting style:\n\n**Prioritizing Comfort and Protection:**\n\n*   **Comfortable Clothes:** Choose something that you can move around in easily. Think t-shirt and jeans, leggings, or a comfortable dress. You'll likely be sitting on the floor or leaning over a table, so comfort is key.\n\n*   **Clothes You Don't Mind Getting a Little Crafty:** While sock-making is relatively clean, a stray thread or a tiny speck of fabric glue could happen. Wear something you don't mind potentially getting a bit messy.\n\n*   **Apron or Smock (Optional):** An apron or smock can provide an extra layer of protection if you're concerned about getting anything on your clothes.\n\n**Adding a Touch of Crafty Style (Optional):**\n\n*   **A craft-themed T-shirt**\n*   **Colorful socks.** This will keep the theme of making things out of socks alive, and it will be fun to look at.\n*   **A fun headband or hair tie:** Something to keep your hair out of your face and add a touch of personality.\n\n**Things to Avoid:**\n\n*   **Anything too precious or delicate:** This is crafting time, not a fancy dinner.\n*   **Loose clothing that could get caught in scissors or sewing equipment:** Safety first!\n\nUltimately, wear what makes you feel comfortable and ready to create! Have fun with your American Girl doll sock outfits!\n",
